# Keeps the per-event progress ledger path tracked in this (dogfood) repo until
# the first real event file is committed. The collaboration-safe-state RFC (A3)
# has code-pact commit its own event ledger so it can dogfood the CI branch-drift
# gate (CONTROL_PLANE_BRANCH_NOT_DRIVEN) — that gate silently skips when the
# ledger is untracked (`git ls-files .code-pact/state/events/` is empty). This
# sentinel makes the path tracked. The ledger readers (readEventFiles /
# readEventFilesAtRev) ignore any name that is not an `<at-compact>-<id>.yaml`
# event file, so `.gitkeep` never affects derived state.
